OL,6,FHSE said there should have been an
OL,7,Fadditional supervisor with the firers
OL,8,Fon the night of the incident, due to
OL,9,Fthe soldiers' lack of experience when
OL,10,Fcarrying out night-time firing.
OL,12,FMandated "night-time" specific safety
OL,13,Ftasks were not carried out prior to
OL,14,Ffiring commencing and incorrect and
OL,15,Funauthorised night vision equipment
OL,16,Fwas being used by some soldiers, it
OL,17,Ffound.
