OL,6,F"The future is one of deep sorrow. Not
OL,7,Fto see Conor grow and find love and
OL,8,Fgive us grandchildren is very sad. He
OL,9,Fwould have been a fabulous father and
OL,10,Fas our only son there is no-one to
OL,11,Fcarry on the family name.
OL,13,F"Socially, I don't go out much anymore
OL,14,Fand Betty (Conor's mother) hardly ever
OL,15,Fgoes out socially except for a meal. I
OL,16,Fmyself could not go back to work after
OL,17,FConor's death. I don't think I want to
OL,18,Fwork anymore as I tend to shun being
OL,19,Faround groups of people.
OL,26,@nD@AOUuD@AOU
