OL,3,CMoD issued with Crown censure over
OL,4,Csoldier's death on training exercise
OL,6,F"We have addressed each of the
OL,7,Ffailings cited in the Crown Censure.
OL,8,FWe took action in the immediate
OL,9,Faftermath and have continued to apply
OL,10,Flessons since. I, as the Army Safety
OL,11,FChampion, am committed to driving the
OL,12,Fnecessary change to reduce all
OL,13,Ftraining risk to the lowest possible
OL,14,Flevel.
OL,16,F"We very much regret Conor's death.
OL,17,FHis legacy will be our continual drive
OL,18,Fto do better. On behalf of the MOD and
OL,19,Fthe Army, I offer my sincere
OL,20,Fcondolences to his family and friends."
